text.tspan: The game is over when all the players have
reached the end. When that happens the victory
screen will pop up and show the placing of
each player.
Throw a dice.
If you land on a questionmark you will
have to anwser the question given to you.
You can use a bought power-up.
If you do lose, Kevin the GooseFrog1 will
come after you!!!
So you win!!
By reaching the end first you win.
Each intersection you can choose which
path you want to take.
Movement is controlled through a digital dice, the
movement has been automated for the players
convenience. You can choose which character toplay as
through the numeral key(1 till 6). On the first screen you
can choose how many players will be playing. A minimum
of 2 and a maximum of 6.
The gameboard is filled with Event block. Some of
which may hinder you while some can benefit you.
Besides the Event blocks there are multiple paths you
can follow to reach the end. Players may choose to go
the long way, which is safer, or the shortcut which
is filled with danger.
The game distinguishes beneficial (questionmark)
and harmful (Red) Event Blocks.
The starting player is decided by the
players themselves.
On the first screen you can choose how many
players will be playing. A minimum of 2 and a
maximum of 6. Then the screen will switch to
the gameboard where fun begins.
(Digital Game)
